FINANCIAL SERVICES CLOUD ADMIN GUIDE
Rollups

Aggregate data from related records. The Rollups feature helps your users to easily view and analyze key information across multiple records, providing a comprehensive overview of data.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions where Financial Services Cloud is enabled

The Rollup By Look Rules (Summary Rollups) feature is available only in the Financial Services Cloud managed package. The Record Rollups feature is available to you in both the Financial Services Cloud managed package and as a standard feature in your org without installing the managed package. Review these essential details about the record rollup feature here:

What’s the Difference Between Record Rollup in Managed Package and the Standard Record Rollup?
RECORD ROLLUPS (MANAGED PACKAGE)	RECORD ROLLUP DEFINITIONS
You can aggregate information from related records for multiple objects at a client or group level. As a result, there is tight coupling between the person account and household use cases.	You can aggregate records from multiple objects or groups.
A record can be associated with only a single household. This restriction prevents the aggregation of the record to multiple households.	You can roll up the same record to multiple households.
You can’t specify filter conditions to filter specific records from an object.	You can specify one or more filter conditions to filter records from an object in the record rollup definition.
For more information about the feature, see Rollups.	For more information about the feature, see Rollup Definitions for Record Rollups in Financial Services Cloud.
